Additionally, a startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, and an alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom. After the event, a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit. Meanwhile, students compare swag items like water bottles and phone chargers.

Representatives from nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths, while students use tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database. Concurrently, an alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews, and a whiteboard lists employers who are scheduling same-day interviews. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom, and a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors near the exit.

Nearby, the engineering society sponsors a resume review table close to the stage. A robotics startup draws attention with a small drone flying above its booth, and healthcare providers showcase community outreach photos to highlight their engagement. Representatives from nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths. A whiteboard lists employers scheduling same-day interviews. As the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names, and career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops. Students also compare swag items like water bottles and phone chargers.
